article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Isaiah Gray had 16 points in Cornell's 95-74 victory against Siena on Tuesday night. Gray also contributed four steals for the Big Red (8-2). Guy Ragland Jr. and Keller Boothby added 13 points apiece. The Saints (2-9) were led by Sean Durugordon, who posted 23 points and 15 rebounds. Zek Tekin added 10 points for Siena. Michael Eley also had nine points and eight rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
